(a) The residents of any unincorporated territory that it is desired to incorporate shall have the right to adopt chapters 30-36 of this title in the manner provided in these chapters;  and thereafter such territory shall be and become incorporated and be governed as set forth in these chapters.  No unincorporated territory shall be incorporated under chapters 30-36 of this title unless such territory contains not less than five thousand (5,000) persons, who shall be actual residents of the territory.

